{"TopicId":85065,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"[VTOL/STOL] Harrier Jump-jet replica (Harrier 2 released!)","CreatedByName":"AlexanderTeaH","CreatedById":111209,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-09-20T18:06:59Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"AlexanderTeaH","CreatedById":111209,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-09-20T18:06:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EI present to you - \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cem\u003Ethe Harrier Jump-jet.\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e7/BAe_Harrier_GR9_ZG502_landing_arp.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022BAe_Harrier_GR9_ZG502_landing_arp.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EAnd here\u0027s my latest replication of it (the Harrier 2)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022//imgur.com/a/BUfmu\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003EJavascript is disabled. View full album\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003EDescription:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003EThe plane can reach speeds just under 200 m/s at sea level and well beyond 500 m/s at an altitude higher than 10 KM. It\u0027s about as maneuverable as a flying brick when compared to my standards (although the real thing would probably envy this kind of maneuverability ), but, it\u0027s not just a horizontally flying brick, it\u0027s also a VTOL. This is where it excels, as you\u0027ll clearly see if you look at the top of the plane where the 10 ASAS modules are located. Hovering force can be reached between 2/3 and 3/3 throttle. And yes, it does fit through the tunnel (if you\u0027re \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003EMareczex333 \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003Eor a fan of him, you\u0027ll know what I mean). Flying the thing with the SAS off is possible, but I recommend keeping it on as the craft likes to slip even during the slightest of rolls.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAction groups:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003E1 - Main Engines\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003E2 - VTOL engine\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/zqoz1wu2qskfc33/Harrier.craft?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EHarrier 1\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/3sy38opzc5fhrnj/Harrier%202.craft?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EHarrier 2\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:36px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cem\u003EEnjoy \u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222014-09-23T14:26:39Z\u0022 title=\u002209/23/2014 02:26  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 23, 2014\u003C/time\u003E by AlexanderTeaH\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlexanderTeaH","CreatedById":111209,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-09-21T07:04:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EUpdated post to make it more user friendly.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jetenginestar","CreatedById":77797,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-09-21T19:54:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe amount of ASAS for this craft is too damn high xD\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlexanderTeaH","CreatedById":111209,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-09-22T12:11:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jetenginestar\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Jetenginestar\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EThe amount of ASAS for this craft is too damn high xD\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI agree. I\u0027m working on reducing the amount of ASAS to a more reasonable amount and will be publishing a second, revised version of my Harrier.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LvL","CreatedById":109145,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-09-22T12:38:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ethat\u0027s a really nice craft! I really like how you did the intakes. rep for you!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlexanderTeaH","CreatedById":111209,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-09-22T15:16:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022oarum\u0022 data-cite=\u0022oarum\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003Ethat\u0027s a really nice craft! I really like how you did the intakes. rep for you!\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThanks! I\u0027m redoing the wings to more closely replicate the real thing. Stay tuned!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlexanderTeaH","CreatedById":111209,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-09-22T16:08:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EUpdated post with a second Harrier which has a different wing design.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}